## What This Document Is About

This guide explains how users access AFCON matches through our web promo links. We'll cover the different experiences users might have and why those differences exist.

**No technical jargon - just clear explanations of what happens from a user's perspective.**

---

## How Users Get to Watch AFCON

When a user clicks a promo link (from WhatsApp, Instagram, SMS, etc.), our system needs to:

1. **Identify the user** - Get their phone number
2. **Check subscription** - See if they're already paying for AFCON
3. **Guide them** - Either show matches (if subscribed) or help them subscribe first
4. **Deliver content** - Give them a streaming link to watch

The experience differs based on:
- ‚úÖ Whether we can detect their phone number automatically
- ‚úÖ Whether they already have an active AFCON subscription

---

## The 3 User Journeys

### Journey 1: Existing Subscriber (Best Experience) ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê
**Who:** Users already paying for AFCON  
**Network:** On MTN data  
**Time:** ~25 seconds from click to watching  
**Steps:** Click link ‚Üí Brief loading ‚Üí Pick match ‚Üí Watch!

### Journey 2: New Subscriber with Good Network ‚≠ê‚≠ê
**Who:** Users not yet subscribed  
**Network:** On MTN data (we can detect their phone automatically)  
**Time:** ~1-2 minutes  
**Steps:** Click link ‚Üí Brief loading ‚Üí See matches ‚Üí Subscribe ‚Üí Pick match ‚Üí Watch!

### Journey 3: New Subscriber on WiFi ‚≠ê
**Who:** Users not yet subscribed  
**Network:** On WiFi or weak signal (can't detect phone automatically)  
**Time:** ~3-5 minutes  
**Steps:** Click link ‚Üí Brief loading ‚Üí See matches ‚Üí Enter phone manually ‚Üí Subscribe ‚Üí Pick match ‚Üí Watch!

---

## Understanding the Technology (Simple Terms)

### What is "Header Enrichment" (HE)?
Think of it like caller ID for the internet. When someone on MTN network visits our website, MTN's network can tell us their phone number automatically - the user doesn't need to type it.

**How it works:**
- User is on MTN mobile data
- MTN network sends hidden information to our website
- We use a helper system called "MagicBox" to read this information
- MagicBox gives us the phone number
- User doesn't type anything!

### What is "MagicBox"?
MagicBox is MTN's special system that captures phone numbers from network data. Think of it as a translator between MTN's network and our website.

**Why we need it:**
- Our website can't read MTN network data directly (not yet)
- MagicBox can read it and tell us the phone number
- Every user gets sent to MagicBox first (takes ~8 seconds)
- MagicBox either succeeds (gets the phone) or fails (can't detect it)

### What is "DUI"?
DUI stands for "Direct User Interface" - it's MTN's subscription page where users pay for AFCON access.

**What happens there:**
- User enters payment details
- MTN charges their account
- Subscription activated
- User comes back to our website

**Important:** We don't control DUI - it's MTN's system, not ours.

### What is the "Skip Button"?
When users aren't subscribed yet, they see AFCON matches with a "Skip" button.

**Why it exists:**
- Some users want to pick a match before subscribing
- Some users want to subscribe first, then browse matches
- Some users want to verify/change their phone number
- It gives users control over their journey

