### User Distribution (Estimated)
Based on typical MTN Nigeria user behavior:

| Journey | User Type | % of Total | Time to Watch | Satisfaction |
|---------|-----------|-----------|---------------|--------------|
| Journey 1 | Existing subscribers on MTN | 20-30% | 25 seconds | ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê |
| Journey 2 | New users on MTN data | 40-50% | 1.5 minutes | ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê |
| Journey 3 | New users on WiFi | 30-40% | 3-5 minutes | ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê |

### Revenue Opportunities

**Journey 1 (Existing Subscribers):**
- ‚úÖ Already generating recurring revenue
- üéØ Focus: Retention and engagement
- üí∞ Value: High LTV (lifetime value)

**Journey 2 (New on MTN Data):**
- ‚úÖ High conversion rate potential
- üéØ Focus: Convert to subscribers
- üí∞ Value: New subscriber acquisition
- üìä Best for aggressive marketing campaigns

**Journey 3 (New on WiFi):**
- ‚ö†Ô∏è Lower conversion rate (more friction)
- üéØ Focus: Reduce abandonment
- üí∞ Value: Still converts (content-driven)
- üìä Good for retargeting campaigns

### Marketing Insights

**For SMS/WhatsApp Campaigns:**
- Target mobile users (Journey 1 & 2)
- Best time: Daytime when users are mobile
- Higher conversion expected

**For Social Media (Instagram/Facebook):**
- Mix of Journey 2 & 3 (depends on user location)
- Many users browse on WiFi at home
- Need compelling content to overcome Journey 3 friction

**For Email Campaigns:**
- Mostly Journey 3 (users open emails on WiFi)
- Lower conversion rate expected
- Need stronger value proposition

### Cost Per Acquisition (CPA)

| Journey | Abandonment Risk | Support Tickets | Effective CPA |
|---------|------------------|-----------------|---------------|
| Journey 1 | Very Low | Very Low | N/A (already subscribed) |
| Journey 2 | Low | Low | Baseline |
| Journey 3 | Medium | Medium | ~1.5-2x Journey 2 |

